Sure! Here's a JavaScript function that capitalizes the first letter of every word in a string:

```javascript
function capitalizeFirstLetter(string) {
  return string.replace(/\b\w/g, char => char.toUpperCase());
}
```

This function uses the `replace` method with a regular expression to find the first character of each word (`\b\w`) and converts it to uppercase using the `toUpperCase` method.

You can use this function like this:

```javascript
const str = "hello world";
const capitalizedStr = capitalizeFirstLetter(str);
console.log(capitalizedStr); // "Hello World"
```

This will capitalize the first letter of each word in the string.
